cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper discusses the application of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) in computer vision, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation schemes, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) to address the insufficient training data problem. The proposed framework, Multiple Instance Learning Convolutional Neural Networks (MILCNN), involves weakly supervised learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the state-of-the-art performance on benchmark datasets, which is a common evaluation metric in neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
